briefings.executiveSummary: Today's highlights: Meta Acquires AI Startup Manus for Agent Integration, AI Agents Automate Psychological Drawing Tests with 85% Expert Accuracy, AI's 2025 Vibe Check: Hype Meets Reality.

items.title: Meta Acquires AI Startup Manus for Agent Integration
items.tldr: Meta acquired AI startup Manus and will integrate its agents into Facebook, Instagram, and WhatsApp alongside Meta AI.
whyItMatters: Shows Meta's aggressive push into AI agents beyond chatbots
Indicates consolidation where big tech acquires specialized AI startups

whatToTry.description: Monitor Meta's developer docs for new agent APIs or integration points.
whatToTry.note: Consider how agent-based features could enhance user engagement in your product.

sources.title: Meta just bought Manus, an AI startup everyone has been talking about

items.title: AI Agents Automate Psychological Drawing Tests with 85% Expert Accuracy
items.tldr: Researchers created a multi-agent AI system that analyzes House-Tree-Person drawings with 85% similarity to expert interpretations, offering standardized psychological assessment.
whyItMatters: Enables scalable, consistent mental health screening without human bias
Shows how multi-agent systems can reduce AI hallucinations in sensitive domains

whatToTry.description: Experiment with multi-agent workflows for complex multimodal tasks. Separate visual analysis from interpretation agents to improve accuracy.
whatToTry.note: Consider how role specialization in AI agents could improve your product's reliability

sources.title: From Visual Perception to Deep Empathy: An Automated Assessment Framework for House-Tree-Person Drawings Using Multimodal LLMs and Multi-Agent Collaboration

items.title: AI's 2025 Vibe Check: Hype Meets Reality
items.tldr: AI's 2025 hype cycle peaked with massive funding, then faced scrutiny over sustainability, safety, and business models.
whyItMatters: Investors are shifting focus from pure growth to sustainable unit economics.
Products must now demonstrate clear safety and ROI to secure funding.

whatToTry.description: Audit your AI product's unit economics and safety documentation before your next funding round.
whatToTry.note: Prepare a one-pager on your model's energy usage, data lineage, and cost-per-inference.

sources.title: 2025 was the year AI got a vibe check

items.title: AI Go Solvers Find New Moves, Reveal Human-AI Strategy Gaps
items.tldr: New research shows AI Go solvers using relevance-zone techniques can discover rare patterns and alternative solutions to classic life-and-death problems, but still differ from human strategic priorities.
whyItMatters: Demonstrates how specialized AI search techniques (RZS) can uncover novel, non-obvious solutions even in constrained problem spaces.
Highlights a persistent gap where AI optimizes for immediate survival while humans optimize for long-term territory - a key insight for strategy AI design.

whatToTry.description: Explore the relevance-zone pattern table concept for your own constrained decision problems. When building AI for games, strategy, or planning, consider implementing a 'relevance zone' to focus search on critical areas rather than brute force.
whatToTry.code:
# Pseudo-concept for a relevance-zone helper
# 1. Identify critical variables/areas in your problem state
# 2. Restrict Monte Carlo Tree Search or similar to those zones
# 3. Build a pattern table of successful zone configurations
whatToTry.note: The code and data are available for study, offering a concrete implementation of these search techniques.

sources.title: A Study of Solving Life-and-Death Problems in Go Using Relevance-Zone Based Solvers
